  "preflight": [
    {
      "op": "log",
      "note": "Section-submenu state (washcentral-sidebar-collapsed-v5) is a SHARED-PROFILE toggle and is nondeterministic on the live tenant: probing on July 11 saw the Customer Portal hub load both collapsed (content shifted ~219px left, the Portal Overview / Access & Security section submenu removed from layout) and expanded across separate fresh loads. This lesson's cross-module navigation genuinely requires the section submenu (step 7 clicks the 'Portal Overview' submenu link back from Access & Security; step 8 clicks the Digital rail then the 'Mobile App Users' submenu link). To make the take deterministic, the FIRST timeline click is an `unless: sidebarExpanded`-guarded genuine click of the app's own 'Expand sidebar' control (title=\"Expand sidebar\", bottom-left), postcondition sidebarExpanded: it fires only when the profile loaded collapsed, only ever EXPANDS (never collapses), and is skipped entirely when already expanded. This is a genuine in-app view-toggle click (the app, not the engine, persists the preference), never a storage write by the engine. Every subsequent page in the chain was probe-verified to preserve the expanded state on load (Access via the Access & Security hub card, Overview via the submenu link, portal-members via the Digital rail, mobile-users via the submenu link — all rendered .app without 'sidebar-collapsed'). sidebarExpanded is asserted after the guarded click and again after each cross-module navigation. All pointer moves, callouts, and highlights resolve LIVE rects / logged geometry, so they track the expanded layout the guarded click guarantees; only the camera keyframes use fixed expanded coordinates. NEVER navigate to login.html: it de-authenticates the shared profile. Preview Portal (onclick=previewPortal, opens the member-facing sign-in) and Copy (onclick=copyPortalUrl) are pointed-at only, never clicked (residuals R1/R2)."
    }
  ],
